      "name": "Introduction",
      "intro_markdown": "For many people Indian cuisine is synonymous with the food of the Mughal shahs, the illustrious rulers of most of India from the sixteenth to the nineteenth century. And, while it is true that a wonderful gastronomic revival took place during their reign – bringing us famous dishes such as korma and biryani – it must be remembered that there is far, far more to Indian food than curries alone.",
