      "name": "Pickles, Chutneys and Raitas",
      "intro_markdown": "In warm climates it is essential to find ways of preserving foodstuffs and prevent spoiling. As such, Indian pickles and chutneys are more than mere accompaniments – they are an intrinsic part of India's gastronomic heritage. Vital components of any meal, a fiery pickle made with chillies can increase the heat of a dish, while mild fruit chutneys or yoghurt-based raitas provide a cooling touch.",
